This is the first picture you see when you walk into my house.  I was my Grandad’s “best buddy” and I revered him.  It’s a special thing in life to know someone has your back unequivocally.  I knew for every moment of my life that my Grandad would be there for me at the drop of a dime, no questions asked.  He lived as full a life as anyone could imagine.  He was as secure in himself as anyone has ever been.  He never met a stranger.  We shared the gift of recovery and he was monumentally influential in my getting sober at 25.  It’s hard to miss someone who left such an impact on your world that you’ll never be without them, but we’ll miss him anyway.  I love you, Grandad.
Grandad’s grandkids L to R: Laynie Claire “My Princess Fair” Sara Charlene “My Beauty Queen” Zachary Charles “The Apple of My Eye” and Jacob Tucker “My Best Buddy”

I never intended for my show to be a “family program.” It’s pretty well-documented that I don’t even have kids.  Sentiments like this, however, seem to dominate my conversations with listeners.  I am BEYOND thankful that so many of you listen & participate with your kids.  I think it’s super cool and am HONORED to be part of your lives.  I’m still perplexed how it happened, but I will  wear the “family show” badge with pride.  For the millionth time,  THANK YOU for helping me live my dreams.
-JT

Most of you don’t know, but I was quite ill in 2022.  It was a months long process of investigation with many doctors and specialists.  My work suffered, I was on my back most of every day, unable to exercise.  I’m happy to report that after 18 months I am feeling even better than before I got sick.  I have some problems that I’ll deal with for the rest of my life, but those pale in comparison to my many blessings.  Through it all the guy in this pic has been my rock.  I lived on his couch for 3 months.  He drove me to countless doctor appointments, emergency rooms and sometimes even to work.  My father is many things (not all of them are my favorites 😜), but one of his best qualities is strength in crisis.  I’m so thankful for you @sasbro43 and I’m thankful we moved on to better memories in 2023.  Here’s to even more in ‘24!  Love!

Radio Personality & Brand Manager @JackFMDFW 
Asst. Brand Manager 98.7 The Spot
